24/01/2011
TOKYO, Japan -- Bulgarian Prime Minister Boyko Borisov is in Tokyo where he met on Sunday (January 23rd) with Japan's Crown Prince Naruhito. 
They discussed opportunities to strengthen bilateral ties and praised their traditionally friendly relations. 
They also talked about prospects for developing relations in the fields of politics, economy and energy, especially when it comes to new technologies and green energy. 
Borisov leaves Japan on Wednesday. 
(Focus, BTA, Darik - 23/01/11)
